.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "August 2023" "Simple Shell Manual" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A simple UNIX command interpreter (shell)
.SH SYNOPSIS
simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is a command interpreter that provides a basic interface for users to interact with their UNIX-like operating system. It reads and executes commands from the user, supports basic shell functionalities, and includes built-in commands such as cd, echo, env, help, and exit.
.SH USAGE
simple_shell is invoked by running the executable file "shelly" or "shelly" followed by an optional file containing shell commands to be executed.
.SH OPTIONS
The simple_shell does not support any command line options.
.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
The simple_shell supports the following built-in commands:
.IP "cd [DIRECTORY]" 4
Change the current working directory to the specified directory.
.IP "echo [TEXT]" 4
Display the specified text on the standard output.
.IP "env" 4
Display the current environment variables.
.IP "exit [STATUS]" 4
Exit the shell with an optional exit status.
.IP "help" 4
Display information about the built-in commands and their usage.
.IP "history" 4
Display the history of user input in the shell.
.SH SEE ALSO
.Sh "shelly(1)"
